<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98771244316220></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98771244316220><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=4828&mid=98771244316220>Why?</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=4828&mid=98771244316220#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Apr 19th 4:34 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[1.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I just don't understand why verant decided to make the "epic" weapons.&nbsp;&nbsp;They are not overly hard to obtain, and don't blow away weapons that drop now in stats.  Plus how is it special if so many high levels have the epics?  What are they gonna do with all the time they spend now? They can't quest for better weapons, because if verant did they would get complaints from people like the ones above me that the epics aren't the best weapons.  Yes I think Verant should have made new quests for each class of high levels, but not have called them epic weapons. The "epic" weapon should only be one per class per server, as it isn't really "epic" if all people 55+ have one.  <br>                            Lost soul of the North<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
