<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100035990259279></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100035990259279><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=4828&mid=100035990259279>RE: Why?</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=4828&mid=100035990259279#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=73658><span id=Sage>DavivMcD</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>200 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Sep 13th 1:45 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Because they were pretty much the best weapons you could get at the time they were made (they came with Kunark, not Velious, where most of the weapons that are 'better' than the epics are dropped) Besides that, who says a weapon like this is better than an epic? It's not all about the damage ratio. Besides the epics having a sweet ratio, awesome stats, and an interesting and powerful proc, as well as many having a unique and nifty effect, Verant might have made these to discourage the constant barrage of twinks going around getting the best of everything just by shouting "I've got 500K! Looking to buy any uber items I could never hope to get on my own!". The epic quests, which apparently are not "overly hard" (ever try the cleric epic?) are an interesting addition to the role-playing factor of the game. Questing for the most powerful weapon for your class (read my post again if you still think other weapons are better just cuz they have a better ratio) would seem to be very fun to do. As for Velious weapons that actually are better than epics (things like primal velium and pretty much any weapon that drops off Vulak'Aerr), you really expected that Verant would make a new expansion and have weapons and armor that's no better than the existing stuff? I don't think people would whine if Verant makes new quest weapons that are much better than the epics; instead I would expect everyone to whine if Verant DIDN'T make anything better than the epics. In fact, there are going to be new epic type weapons for every class included in the shadows of luclin expansion. What do you do when you spend all your time getting your epic and Verant makes new and better weapons? Pardon my French, but quit yer bitchin' and go out and get those weapons, duh! If you really valued all that time spent on a game that much, maybe you shouldn't be playing this game at all. Well, I'm done ranting and raving for now. Don't take all this personally, whoever wrote the original post; this is just a general attack on all the 'whinos' out there.<br>&nbsp;<br>Daviv McD 26th Dwarf Rogue<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=13233" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=13233</a></td></tr>
